Here are both approaches:

**1. Navigate with a string ID**

```csharp
// From ProductListPage or its ViewModel
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
```

**2. Navigate with a full object**

```csharp
var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }   // complex object – must use this overload
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
```

> The single-object overload requires the `Dictionary<string, object>` signature added in .NET MAUI; primitive query-string params are decoded as strings.

---

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product  { get => _product;  set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1 – simple string parameter from the query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
            ProductId = idObj.ToString();

        // Approach 2 – full object passed via the Dictionary overload
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var prodObj) && prodObj is Product p)
            Product = p;

        // Kick off loading if only an ID was provided
        if (Product is null && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(ProductId))
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await SomeService.GetProductByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**Wire up the ViewModel on the page**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;          // Shell resolves IQueryAttributable on the BindingContext
}
```

**Register the route + DI**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs / AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// MauiProgram.cs
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key points**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Navigation** | query string (`?key=val`) | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| **Received as** | `object` (string at runtime) | original CLR type — cast it |
| **Back-nav safe** | Yes (re-parsed from URI) | No (object ref may be null on back) |

Use the **string ID** approach when deep-linking or back-navigation matters; use the **object** approach to avoid a redundant fetch when you already have the data in memory.
